.vite/

# agent-chat: the entire conversations/ tree is per-machine runtime state.
# Session/presence/log files are throwaway. Conversation transcripts and
# archives are user content (the user's actual chats), not skill code, and
# they grow noisy fast. The scripts create the tree on demand, so absence
# from a fresh clone is the expected state.
#
# If you DO want to version a particular conversation (e.g. for a public
# example), force-add the specific edge directory: `git add -f conversations/pair/lumeyon-orion/CONVO.md`
conversations/

# Claude Code's per-machine working state — scheduled task locks, session
# snapshots, settings overrides, etc. Same shape as conversations/: created
# on demand by Claude Code on each clone, not part of the skill source.
# Force-add specific files if a particular Claude Code config (e.g. a
# project-level settings.json with shared permissions) should be versioned.
.claude/
